Text.string: We'll help Rhys when we can, but right now, we've got to get to Athenas. I've got a friend there. We should see what she knows.
Claptrap, tight broadcast to Athenas, callsign “sapphire”.

Yeah! Kinda! I'm guessing you're calling for the same reason Maliwan is trashing our monastery. Well, I don't have it, but I know where it is. Hey—get here soon or you'll miss all the fun. And by “fun”, I mean “getting bulldozed by corporate murder squads”.
We're on our way, just try to... hold out.
Maya... she can hold her own until we get there. She's a Siren, and as badass as they come. Hell, maybe we can convince her to join us.
Ohh, more ladies on Admiral Claptrap's love ship.
Everyone's lookin' at Claptrap! Boo-ya!
Set a course for Athenas, Vault Hunter.
You're here! Right in time for a fight. I'm Maya. Come find me in the market quarter. A battalion of Maliwan troops are trampling my home and I'd appreciate some help, you know, killing them.
Whew! Heh. See you soon.
Thought so. Follow me. We'll meet up with my apprentice, IF she hasn't gotten herself killed.
Attention, stupid pacifist monks! This is Oppressor Traunt. It's not just a title, oppression is my profession. Athenas is now property of the Maliwan Corporation. No trespassing!
I've done worse. A lot worse. Like, seriously.
Fine, but let's call it “grave-borrowing”. Got a reputation to uphold.
Robbing a human grave is on my bucket list.
I'm for it!
I've got my book, and heading your way in a sec. I'm just finishing up some...
This relic's been here since before I was born, but as long as Maliwan knows it's here, Athenas will never be safe.
Nope. Go pack a bag. You get your wish. We're leavin' with the Vault Hunter.
Wait, for real?||I mean, yeah, cool, whatevs. Could be fun. I'll grab my stuff.
The Eridians left messages like these all over the galaxy. I always figured there was a connection between Sirens and Vaults. I can't read it, but it must mean something.
Claptrap! Holy crap, I've heard so much about you!
Wait, what?
Uh, yeah?! When you took on the bullymongs, and Captain Flynt—and the STAIRS?! I make Maya tell me about it all the time!
Have YOU come to the right place! Come, new favorite crew member! Come and hear the story of how MY ASS saved the entire ship!
A new Vault Key fragment. Just holding this makes my skin tingle! That, and I ate one of Marcus's... discount burritos.

You should return to Lilith. I'm sure she and Maya have a lot of “catching up” to do, or whatever it is people with social lives do. No thank you! Give me a sterile room full of surgical equipment any day!
Meet me up on the bridge when you're ready, killer.
Look alive, monks—'cause we're gonna KILL YOU!
Maliwan again. These guys are relentless.
I can kick out a few pirates every month, but a whole corporate battalion? I'm spread too thin. But now you're here.
Secure the square. Once it's safe, we'll ring the bell of peace so the monks can let us through.
Maya! Where's the little one?
Probably finding trouble!
Finding trouble, or causing it. May the six storms protect you.
He's right. I should check on my apprentice. Ava, are you still guarding the library?
Maya! Hey... yes. I am definitely at the library, because you told me to stay there. Here! Because it's where I still am.
Ugh. Keeping Ava in one place is like holding on to quicksilver. But that's why I took her in. Either she was going to get herself killed, or maybe I could train her to... y'know, survive.

Attention, monks of Athenas. This is Captain Traunt. Surrender the Vault Key fragment immediately... or we're gonna downsize your stupidly serene planet. That means we're gonna blow it up! God, I love this company! Form and function!
Getting closer. Let's waste these guys and signal the monks to let us through.
Well, hop on in whenever!
Hell yeah, Vault Hunter! If you'd been around when the invasion started, we just might have held our own. Now ring the bell.

Captain Traunt here. Again. Why are you statue-polishers fighting back, anyway? I mean, I... I thought you were supposed to be all zen and shit. Stop this rebellion immediately, or I'll reduce your tranquil meditation planet to rubble.
Cool if I take this?
Thaaanks, later.
Yeah. I get to kill bad guys pretty much all the time. It's great.
That's me! Would you like an autograph?
There is more to it than that. But not much more.
You're making me sound awesome. I like it.

YES! That's so freakin' cool I want to die instantly. I'm gonna be a Vault Hunter too! Or, I would be, if Maya assigned me more than just guarding a dusty-ass library and staring at water for like a hundred hours.
Sorry, just really boring around here. So! We gonna loot this graveyard or what?
Maya says the monks put Eridium in tombs, so the dead have some spending money in the afterlife. We'll pay 'em back later—like, if we're not also dead.
C'mon.
I can open this tomb up no sweat. What you got, tomb? You got nothin'!
I'm gonna blast you to “inner pieces”! Eh? Hahaha!
I got this one—agh, it's sticky! Why?! Why is it sticky?! Ugh, monks are so weird!
Ohhh, crap!
Attention everyone, this is Captain Traunt! Those monks are in that spooky graveyard. Wipe 'em out and make me proud. Then we'll go out for soft serve! Cones on Traunt!
Maya wants to have all the fun fighting off Maliwan but SCREW THAT! That Traunt guy is the worst and I want to kick his dick off myself!
Last tomb. Then we can go get that fragment. Man, I've been dyin' to get inside that anchorhold ever since I got here. Somethin' about locked doors, man. Makes my palms itch.
I am done playing games, monks. Get ready for some divine judgment, from ME! TRAAAAUNT!
Whatchu got, gate? Nothin', bitch! You got nothin'!
Ava. Go protect the grain storerooms. Let the Vault Hunter take care of Maliwan.
It'll be nice to have someone else here besides my apprentice who hasn't taken an oath of non-violence. Speaking of which...
Ughhh! Got it, Maya. On my way.
All I ever do is protect archives, or storerooms, or sacred whatevers. I'll see ya later, Vault Hunter.
TRAAAAAAUNT!
Vault Hunter! You wasted Traunt? Good riddance.
Oh, was his name Traunt?
My only regret is that I had to stop punching him.
He is dead, that's what matters. But yeah, seriously, the worst.
Ah, he seemed all right. Apart from the whole, uh... oppression business, of course.
I've never been able to use Eridium the way Lilith does, but I found a technique in this book that might change that.
Teach me that right now.
So, Ava. You survived the invasion. Guess all those hours staring at water taught you somethin' after all.
Tch. I can handle myself. I learned to fight WAY before I met you.
Let's spar then, kid.
It's the Siren! Get her!
Oh, you know, I would, but I've got, uh... loot to sort through.
Vault Hunter, check this out.
All yours.
What do you mean, a Siren apprentice?
I can't explain it right now, Lilith. But she's going to be a Siren someday.
We'll talk about this later...
Great work. You do that. Rhys out.
I'M MELTINGGG! Ghrhrgrllrrhrgh!
... karmic realignment.
Uh, that was a... book. Gottagobye!
Huh, empty. Weak—but I know a few more places we can try.
DIE, YOU CORPORATE BASTARDS!||[deep breath] Ancient relaxation exercises. Much better.
This way!
Clear out those troops. I'll be there soon. Just laying out some...
So you're kickin' ass with the Raiders? Guess Lilith had to replace me eventually. Ready for some more action?
Maliwan's full of teched-out nerds. Let's kick 'em in the dick.
You know it. And if you don't know, now you know.
That's why I'm here. Asses. And kicking them.
I was born kicking ass. And I'll die kicking ass.
You spoony monks are pissin' me off! Stick a fork in you, you're DEAD!
I came back from Pandora to protect this place. That was working out pretty good until Maliwan found us.
Let's kill these guys, then loot 'em!
Open up, tomb! Reveal your splendors, or... whatever.
Ratch! I hate ratch! Or is it ratches? Either way... they must die.
Ugh. That's Traunt. Real pain in my ass. So far, he hasn't been able to get into the anchorhold, but... let's not rely on his incompetence.
Huh. Looks like they ate the Eridium... but Maya's gonna need WAY more than that.
What the hell?!

Attention, rebel monks of Athenas. This is Captain Traunt again, uh... I'm losing my freakin' patience, so I'll say this as politely as I can: please consider surrendering while we trample your treasured heritage just 'cause, uh... we're better than you.
Coast's clear. When we're not at war, the bells of peace ring all hours of the day and night. Kind of a nightmare, honestly.
Gahhh! Ratch attack! RUN!
Andddddd, comms open!
This wasn't in my contract!
Ohhoh—big ratch! Big freakin' ratch! Kill it! No mercy, NO MERCY! IT MUST DIE!
Awww, hell yeah! That Eridium... is probably covered in ratch guts. You should pick it up. For... safety.
In case you were wondering, this isn't a complete Vault Key. Why the Eridians split the Keys into fragments is anyone's guess, but the Vault Key on Pandora required three pieces. Still, it's a start.

Now, look, monks. I know you think I'm doing this 'cause I enjoy terrorizing you, but it's actually to make my big brother proud of me! He's a General, y'see, and I got a, heh, HUGE inferiority complex about it. So if I have to burn down your entire monastery to impress him, then... so be it, y'know? You get it, right? You get it.
Suck ittttt!

Okay, so you saw a corporation that was getting curb-stomped by a way bigger and cooler corporation, and you said, “I'm going with team loser-stache”? Come on, work with me here, superfan! This whole beef over the Vaults has been getting mondo views, but it's got a shelf life. Specifically, when you die, so... try to keep it going? Maybe find some better allies? Just a suggestion. Later!
I'm gonna need some Eridium to get into the anchorhold. It'll amp up my Siren powers. On an extremely-related note, how do you feel about grave-robbing?
Good. There's some Eridium hidden in the cemetery. Something tells me Ava's already there. She'll help you out.

I've never actually been inside the anchorhold. It's got Eridian protections around it, but I think I can get around them. There's a passage in my book of ancient Siren techniques. Gonna go grab it since the library's unprotected and I'll catch up with you later.
Maya.
Nice work. Let's chat.
So how was Promethea?
Oh... hey! I was just out here... looting corpses. But, wait—you're a Vault Hunter like Maya USED to be? Go on adventures, save the universe, kill bad guys?
A war-zone. Atlas is getting crushed.
Big city. Felt like home. Atlas has seen better days.
A jungle of concrete and neon. Atlas is on its last gasp.
Great nightlife, lots of craters. But Atlas is getting their arse handed to 'em.
Woah...

There I was! Surrounded by total nimrods, who couldn't tell you the difference between an implosion drive and a sun-baked egg salad sandwich. “Be careful,” I said! “This is high tech stuff!” But noooo, they wouldn't listen to me. They just took off! No regard for safety protocols! Now the whole ship is tearing itself apart! Lilith says, “Oh no. We've got a hull breach.” That's when I made a decision that even the Firehawk herself couldn't make! I chose to throw myself at the danger rather than risk the lives of my friends and crewmates. And I plugged the hole with my own ass!
Wow, it's like bein' in the presence of a real life legend!
I get that a lot.
Takes an ass-kicker to know an ass-kicker.
What can I say? I'm a natural.
Yes! We sent a great many asses to Death.
Oh, that was nice of her! I really put a lot of meself into it.
I believe it. Well, one fragment down, two more to go.
Lilith? What are—oh, dammit!
Bad time?
Save us!
We are doomed.
May the storms protect us.
What will we do?
Cool. Let's get this Eridium to Maya.
Quiet!

Huh. Ava really took a shine to you. Might want to check your pockets. She was a stowaway on one of our seasonal merchant ships. We... crossed paths. She tried to steal my book... and instead of throwing her off a cliff, I decided to train her as my apprentice.
Whuh-guh-gwahagh!
You got the Eridium? Give it here.
Okay, here goes... something.
It's... it's working!
Hooo-ly crap. I feel like I could phaselock a planet right now!
Every journey starts with one step, and your journey ends with death!
Whew, I could get used to that kind of power. Okay, let's get the Key fragment, Vault Hunter.
I should tell you this before I explain it to Lilith. The real reason I took Ava on as an apprentice... she's going to be a Siren. Someday. And I want to make sure she's ready when that happens.
See you up in the stars, Vault Hunter.
Lilith tells me you have acquired a Vault Key fragment. Bring it to me. I shall keep it safe while you gallivant around in search of the other pieces.
Helloooo semi-adult human! I am—
I am through playin' games—unless that game is KILL THE MONKS! That'd be awesome!
So you... want to hear stories... about how cool I am.
Pshh! Yeah!
S'up, killer. Maya says you kicked some major ass.
Ohohhh, man! This guy had everything up in there! Troop movements, supply lines, scouting data... hmm.
Looks like Maliwan's been searching for fragments of the Vault Key themselves, and they've got some leads. A planet called... Athenas?
Athenas? Perfect. Vault Hunter, come up to Sanctuary.
It would be helpful to have another Siren on board.||—Besides you, Lilith. I was still counting you.
Drop pod's ready when you are, VH!
A bandit cult led by a soul-sucking Siren. Inter-corporate war on Promethea. We're in the crap, amigo, no doubt about it. You just keep kickin' ass for Lil. Someone's got to.
The fragment's sealed inside an Eridian anchorhold. The whole monastery was built around it by monks who think it's sacred. Maybe it is, but right now it's attracting the wrong kind of attention.
